               <p>THOMAS CURTIS. I am <rs id="t18280221-196-viclabel1044" type="occupation">apprentice</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-196-victim1160 t18280221-196-viclabel1044"></join> to Mr. Le Grose, a watchmaker. On the 10th of February, about ten o'clock in the morning, my clothes were safe in my box, in the kitchen, and I saw the prisoner looking through the window - I went out, and on returning, at night, missed them;<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182802210113"></xptr>next morning I went to No. 78, St. Martin's-lane, where the prisoner is apprenticed, and found them in his box - his parents live at my master's.</p>
               <p>
            
